  "title": "Continuous Improvement Manager (Aerospace)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Location : Loyang, near pasir ris </strong><br /><strong>Industry : Aviation /Aerospace</strong><br /></p><p>My client is  seeking a high-impact <strong>Continuous Improvement Manager</strong> to drive operational excellence within our <strong>Singapore Aerospace MRO operations</strong>. Reporting closely to the <strong>General Manager</strong>, this role plays a critical part in improving shop-floor performance while ensuring strong alignment with <strong>global Customer Support and corporate transformation initiatives</strong>.</p><p>This role is ideal for a hands-on leader who understands the realities of <strong>MRO operations, Part 145 environments, and safety-critical processes</strong>, and can translate Lean and Six Sigma methodologies into measurable business results.</p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><ul><li><p>Lead and deploy <strong>Lean, Six Sigma, and continuous improvement initiatives</strong> across MRO operations</p></li><li><p>Improve <strong>quality, turnaround time (TAT), cost, and safety</strong> through structured problem-solving</p></li><li><p>Partner the General Manager as a <strong>trusted advisor</strong>, supporting data-driven decision-making</p></li><li><p>Drive local implementation of <strong>corporate Customer Support and digital transformation programs</strong></p></li><li><p>Work closely with <strong>shop-floor teams, planners, engineers, quality, and support functions</strong> to ensure adoption and sustainability</p></li><li><p>Facilitate root cause analysis (PDCA, gap analysis) and coach teams on CI tools</p></li><li><p>Track, analyse, and report <strong>KPIs, project benefits, and operational performance</strong></p></li><li><p>Act as the site focal point for CI escalation and interface with global transformation networks</p></li></ul><p>Requirements</p><ul><li><p><strong>Lean or Six Sigma certification</strong> (Black Belt preferred) with hands-on deployment experience</p></li><li><p><strong>Minimum 5 years’ experience in Aerospace / Aviation MRO</strong>, ideally in a <strong>Part 145</strong> environment</p></li><li><p>Strong understanding of <strong>MRO workflows, regulatory and safety requirements</strong></p></li><li><p>Proven ability to lead cross-functional projects and manage change in complex operations</p></li><li><p>Solid project management skills; <strong>PMP or PRINCE2</strong> certification is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Office; <strong>MS Project</strong> experience preferred</p></li><li><p>Strong analytical, communication, and stakeholder management skills</p></li></ul><p>Why Join my Client</p><ul><li><p>High-visibility role within a <strong>Singapore-based MRO operation</strong></p></li><li><p>Direct impact on operational performance and customer satisfaction</p></li><li><p>Exposure to <strong>global aerospace customer support and digital transformation initiatives</strong></p></li><li><p>Opportunity to shape a strong culture of continuous improvement on the shop floor</p></li></ul>",
